The "Intelligent Gathering of Xiaoxiang" 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opened - Rolling News - Hunan Daily Network - Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily December 10th news (Full media reporter Zhou Zhiheng) On the 9th, the "Intelligent Gathering of Xiaoxiang" 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opened in Zhuzhou.
Wang Cheng, a provincial standing committee member and the minister of the Provincial Party Committee Organization Department, attended the opening ceremony and delivered a speech.
Wang Cheng pointed out that the holding of the talent summit is an important measure to implement the spirit of the Central Talent Work Conference and the 12th Provincial Party Congress, reflecting Hunan's sincerity and efforts in attaching importance to, yearning for, and making good use of talents.
Hunan has a fine tradition of recognizing, loving, and respecting talents, a broad platform to help talent development, and a favorable environment for a better life. In recent years, Hunan has implemented the talent-led development strategy, taken the Lotus Talent Action Plan as a driving force, and established a full chain talent work pattern to cultivate, retain, and use talents, making it a fertile soil for talent growth, a hot land for innovation and entrepreneurship, and a pleasant place for living and working.
Currently, Hunan is comprehensively implementing the "three highs and four news" strategic positioning and mission, further opening the door to talent recruitment, and providing better policies, more resources, and better conditions for talent innovation and entrepreneurship. The province hopes that outstanding talents from all sectors will gather their wisdom and strength for Hunan's high-quality development.
The event has set up exhibitions in Changsha, Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, and the Hunan Free Trade Zone, with the Department of Science and Technology, the Department of Industry and Information Technology, and the Department of Human Resources and Social Security releasing lists of key scientific and technological innovation needs in advanced manufacturing industries, catalogs of personnel needs in intelligent manufacturing industries, and catalogs of personnel needs for young intellectuals in the intelligent manufacturing industry.
48 large enterprises such as CRRC, CNR Heavy Machinery, and CSCEC came to recruit talent, and nearly 1,000 recent graduates and social talents in related fields participated in the talent project docking.